title: Eagles 7-time Pro Bowl LT Jason Peters leaves with injury
text:
Eagles 7-time Pro Bowl LT Jason Peters carted off with back injury; return questionable THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   9:33   9:33   
Organizations: 
North Carolina (541) 

CHARLOTTE, North Carolina — The Philadelphia Eagles say left tackle Jason Peters is questionable to return to Sunday night's game at Carolina with what is described as a lower back injury. 
The seven-time Pro Bowler was blocking Jared Allen when he crumpled to the grass with 5:21 left in the opening quarter, laying face down until medical staffers could come to his aid. Teammates gathered around him as he was loaded onto a cart and several came by to speak with him before the cart headed to the tunnel for X-rays.
